# WSL Development Journal

When working on this project in WSL/Cursor, assume chat history may disappear.

- Before substantial work, read `DEVELOPMENT_LOG.md` and `开发者日志.md`.
- After every meaningful milestone, append a concise handoff note to one of those files before ending the turn.
- A meaningful milestone includes: root-cause found, plan changed, file/path moved, config changed, bug partially fixed, blocker discovered, or next step clarified.
- Prefer small iterative diary updates over one big recap at the end.
- Each note should capture:
  - current goal
  - what changed
  - key files/symbols touched
  - blockers/risks
  - the most likely next step
- If the task changes priorities, update the priority section in `开发者随笔.md`.
- Do not finish a substantial coding/debugging turn without leaving an updated handoff note.
